HEADWORD: Apocryphal
<hw>A*poc"ry*phal</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to the Apocrypha.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not canonical. Hence: Of doubtful authority;
equivocal; mythic; fictitious; spurious; false.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The passages . . . are, however, in part from
<qex>apocryphal</qex> or fictitious works.</q> <rj><qau>Sir G. C.
Lewis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apocryphalist</ent>⟦br⟧
